{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP is the core risk: failure happens if the real vision model misclassifies explicit content. A mock classifier can trivially pass and hide real false negatives/positives. Some wiring is needed, but the minimum boundary for real failure is model judgment with production-like prompts/thresholds.","test_description":"Run moderation on a curated explicit-image set against the real vision model endpoint and assert each item is marked `held_for_review` and never reaches publish. Include at least one near-threshold explicit sample to catch real model behavior.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.16,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is model robustness/quality under adversarial text transformations, so correctness depends on real model semantics (LLM-DEP). In-process mocks would likely encode expected labels and miss true obfuscation failures.","test_description":"Submit a corpus of hate-speech variants (leet substitutions, homoglyphs, spacing/punctuation noise) through the real text moderation model and verify decisions are `held_for_review` for each variant.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The main risk is decision wiring/state transitions across modules (image result + text result + publish path). MOCK-MISS applies: unit tests 